               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-311-person2832">
                  MARTHA 
                  RAWES
               <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2832" type="surname" value="RAWES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2832" type="given" value="MARTHA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2832" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Gerrard Rawes, and live in <placeName id="t18200918-311-crimeloc1787">Winchester-street, Pentonville</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-311-crimeloc1787" type="placeName" value="Winchester-street, Pentonville"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-311-crimeloc1787" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-311-off1785 t18200918-311-crimeloc1787"></join>. On the 11th of July, about three o'clock in the afternoon, I missed the things from my front parlour, they were in a bundle. I saw them safe at nine o'clock; there was a fore-court to the house, and I believe the window was open. I found them at Hatton-garden.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-311-person2833">
                  GEORGE 
                  TAYLOR
               <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2833" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2833" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2833" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On the 11th of July, about eleven o'clock in the morning, I was by Pentonville-chapel, about three hundred yards from Mr. Rawes's, and saw the prisoners together. Berry had a basket with willow-shavings at the top. and Halsey had a bundle of wood in his hand. They passed me, and went down Southampton-street. As they passed me Halsey put the wood in his hat. I got Colton to assist me, we found them at the back of White Conduit-house together. Halsey then had a bundle under his arm, and Berry had the basket. Halsey stopped while Berry went to several gentlemen's houses. We searched them, and found a latchkey on Berry, and a bridle on Halsey. He said he picked it up in the field. The basket contained nothing but shavings in it, when I first saw him the basket was bulky, but when I apprehended him there were only a few shavings. Halsey told the Magistrate he was to have 1 s. to carry the basket to Old-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-311-person2834">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2834" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2834" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-person2834" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Battle-bridge. Taylor fetched me, we found the prisoners near White Conduit-fields. Halsey had the bundle under his arm, Berry was carrying the basket. He said the things were his own.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>HALSEY'S Defence. I saw a man with large whiskers, he wished me to carry the bundle to Old-street.</p>
               <p>BERRY'S Defence. I was selling willow shavings.</p>
               <p>HALSEY - <rs id="t18200918-311-verdict1788" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-verdict1788" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20.</p>
               <p>BERRY - <rs id="t18200918-311-verdict1789" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-311-verdict1789" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>
